            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001181_0001" n="0001"/>
<lb/><opener><dateline rend="right"><placeName>Hadley Green</placeName> <date when="1858-01-19">19 January<!-- Change line info as appropriate --><!-- Begin each line with <lb/> as here --> 
<lb/> 1858</date></dateline><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
<lb/>    
<lb/><salute>My Dear Sir,</salute></opener><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
<lb/><p rend="right">I think I had
<lb/>acknowledged the
<lb/>receipt of your
<lb/>favour containing
<lb/>the note from
<lb/><persName>Lady Cherurynd</persName> before
<lb/>your last came
<lb/>to hand but certainly
<lb/>not before it was
<lb/>due - and while

	<pb facs="liv_001181_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>thanking you for
<lb/>the courtesy you
<lb/>showed in directing
<lb/>me to send my
<lb/>things to your brothers
<lb/>warehouse it has
<lb/>occurred to me
<lb/>that possible he
<lb/>has some of the
<lb/>articles we need
<lb/>as presents and
<lb/>that if we got
<lb/>them from him
<lb/>it would save all
<lb/>the carriage

	<pb facs="liv_001181_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/><unclear cert="low">has</unclear> he <unclear cert="low">leads and brainsoire</unclear>
<lb/>&amp; ammunition such as
<lb/>are used in the West
<lb/>African trade, if so
<lb/>I would like to arrange
<lb/>with him - or another on getting 
<lb/>samples - I am
<lb/>proceeding on the
<lb/>hope of being excused
<lb/>if I am thinking
<lb/>of him too meanly
<lb/>and that if he is
<lb/>not actually engaged
<lb/>in interpreting <unclear cert="low">beads</unclear>

	<pb facs="liv_001181_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>he may give me a
<lb/>hint as to finding
<lb/>a man who will
<lb/>deal fairly with me
<lb/>instead. I could get
<lb/>them lin London but
<lb/>the carriage might
<lb/>be saved by getting
<lb/>them in <placeName>Liverpool</placeName>
<lb/>Hoping you will not
<lb/>imitate my bad
<lb/>example in correspondence
</p>
<lb/><closer><salute>I am yours most
<lb/>truly - </salute><!-- Change as appropriate -->
<lb/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed></closer><!-- Change as appropriate --> 



            </div>
        </body>
